header: Use PST Repair Software When Scanpst Tool Fails
bio: MS Outlook comes with inbuilt repair utility which is commonly known as Inbox Repair Tool or Scanapst.exe. This effective tool is used for repairing damaged or corrupt PST files. Generally, users executes Scanpst tool in order to repair the damaged PST files. But at times it happens that tools fails to respond and you are unable to repair the corruption. This inbuilt tool has some limitation due to which it fails in certain conditions like oversized PST files. In such conditions you need to use effective third-party Outlook PST Repair Software using which you can easily repair the corrupt PST files.

header: The Trick is to Keep Moving.
media + web + social change + big thoughts + critical thinking
bio: Hi, I'm Austra (pronounced Ow-Stra). I live in Troy, NY.I love media, design and new technology and have a strong social entrepreneurial spirit. My passions get stoked around education, culture, place, and class, and the role media and new technologies play in remedying or exacerbating these issues. I've studied everything from video production and web design, to major facets of the human condition such as the foundations of western civilization, critical thinking, communication theory, Plato's major works, how memes spread, biological anthropology, and human variation. I'm still studying, still soaking up knowledge where ever I can.Throughout my life I've thrived in leadership roles in creative environments focused on people. I've worked in communications at a Boston law school and as sales and marketing manager for an web startup. I spent a glorious four years at Arts Engine, an indie media company in NYC, doing outreach around our documentaries, managing content and design of our online community MediaRights.org, and helping to run four consecutive Media That Matters film festival of social-issue shorts. In college, I was Chief Videographer for our school's news channel. Even in highschool I worked as an after-school counselor and site art director for underprivileged youth. Since I was 15 I worked at my Latvian youth summer camp, growing from "kitchen slime" to counselor to folk dance teacher, and last summer was promoted to the number-two-in-charge position of Program Director.I work best combining these interests and experiences together to create outside-the-box approaches and unconventional connections. My friends say I'm addicted to the internet, but really, I just see the endless potential it holds. I love figuring out multi-channel, robust social marketing strategies around targeted business goals and tracking those successes while learning what improvements need to be made. Call it social media, call it old fashioned communication, call it.. creativity. Call it the ancient art of storytelling. Moving people with meaning.<--- This is me. Ready to do something BIG. Interested in joining me?Oh, and my hair is not nearly as long and disheveled as this photo suggests.

header: INNOVAZIONE E' CONSIDERARE OGNI PUNTO DI ARRIVO UN PUNTO DI PARTENZA
bio: Dal 1990 è ricercatore nel settore ''automotive'' consegue alcuni brevetti. Tra essi la ''batteria polifunzionale'', precursore delle moderne batterie con elettronica di controllo integrata; in uso oggi nei piu' comuni dispositivi di comunicazione e nei veicoli a trazione ibrida o elettrica. Dal 2000 è ricercatore nel settore della ''termografia'' nei Controlli Non Distruttivi (CND), per la manutenzione predittiva negli impianti di Gassificazione IGCC. Nel 2003 dirige il primo team di sviluppo del prototipo termografico AVIS (Advanced Vision Inspection System). Nel 2005 gli impianti di Gassificazione api Energia - nelle Marche - e ERG Isab Energy - in Sicilia - sono stati i primi nel mondo ad adottare la nuova tecnologia termografica AVIS. Nel 2006 e' primo classificato nella sessione ''Poster'' alla quinta edizione del convegno internazionale VGR tenutosi a Pisa, organizzato da APAT, ARPAL, Consiglio Nazionale Ingegneri, Ministero dell'Ambiente, Ministero dei Trasporti, Ministero dell'Interno, Ministero della Salute, e Universita' di Pisa con la pubblicazione "La termografia nelle applicazioni energetiche". Nel 2010 e' cofondatore della rivista THE WEEK, ''il primo settimanale degli italiani nati dopo il 1 gennaio 1970'', insieme a Mario Adinolfi, Marco Esposito, Marco De Amicis, Gabriele Rossi, Timoteo Carpita, Cristian Umbro, Alessia Fedele e Giovanna Giampa. Nel 2011 fonda il nuovo operatore postale inPoste.it licenziatario esclusivo della "Raccomandata Elettronica", selezionata innovazione dell'anno per il settore Egovernemt e servizi al cittadino. Inserito tra gli innovatori 2011/2012 dell'Agenzia Innovazione presso la Presidenza del Consiglio dei Ministri, partecipa alla missione in Cina e al Convengo Nazionale dell'Innovazione 2011 presso il Politecnico di Torino

Claudio E. Cabrera is a 29 year-old award-winning journalist and digital marketer based out of the Inwood section of New York City.
In 2005, Cabrera began his journey in journalism writing for the weekly newspaper, the New York Amsterdam News. Since, he's written for various weekly newspapers, magazines and online sites compiling over 150 news clips. He's profiled the likes of Alonzo Mourning, Mayor Michael Bloomberg, Shaquille O'Neal and Rev. Al Sharpton to name a few.
In 2006, Cabrera was one of 20 journalists selected out of a pool of 60 to attend the NCEW Minority Writers Seminar in Nashville, Tennessee where he learned a great deal from various columnists from across the country. Cabrera also won an award from the Independent Press Association in 2006 for 'Best Article on a Social, Racial, or Immigration' issue. The piece focused on the exorbitant rates phone company MCI charges families of inmates for phone calls in NY state.
In February of 2008, Cabrera was selected among a host of students from New York's top colleges and universities appearing as an analyst on NBC's "Super Tuesday" Democratic primary coverage.
After graduating from Brooklyn College in the same year with a Bachelor's Degree in Journalism, he went on to work for "the stock market for sports tickets," Yoonew, and helped grow their web operations through social media community building, editorial and SEO. It was his first job after graduation.
In 2010, Cabrera took over as the lead editor at NewsOne.com, where he struck partnerships with major news sites, helped create an event at the White House in which President Obama spoke at, and led the charge in growing the site exponentially within a year and a half.
Within the last two years, Cabrera has moved into the field of technology becoming an SEO expert and growing brands such as EURweb, NewsOne.com, Loop21.com and Blackenterprise.com. He grew all of these sites over 100 percent in his time working with each.
Currently, he is the Audience Engagement and Marketing Manager at BlackEnterprise.com where he has grown traffic over a 100 percent.
He was honored by Folio Magazine as a 2013 "Audience Development All-Star" and has been selected to speak on a panel at South by Southwest in 2014.

Christopher Ellis is an author who challenges the very foundation of our perceptions and beliefs. His provocative writing strikes at the very heart of everything we take for granted on a daily basis and draws us into questioning the nature of our realtionships with what we've come to beleive is the world 'around us'.
Writing from a parabolic perspective, with an allegorical twist, Ellis approaches head-on our concepts of Belief, Faith, Time, Nature, Life, Motion and Death. He does so not in an attempt to reinvent the wheel, but to show us that we're already quite familiar with most everything we need to make the adjustments in become better Human Beings.
"We already have the building blocks, we already have the tools for change, yet for most of our lives we've followed the methods of others regaring assembly. I'm just trying to show that if you rearrange your blocks in a different order, the blocks you've had all along, and your willing to readdress the nature of the relationship you have with your blocks, then you might find something extraordinary already within you."
 
Ellis' first book, 'The Devil and a Tree' will be available October, 2012.

Watching him grow up has been an amazing experience since he arrived in mid 2010. My 'other' work is website and print design. I now specialise in design / builds for individuals / small businesses and frequently use WordPress / Tumblr for them. 
Rest: When I'm not bashing away at a computer keyboard, I spend time with my little family; going out for walks and mini adventures. I also try to watch as many new films as I can, whether big budget Hollywood movies or small independents. As with most things after a family is created, our cinema going as dramatically dipped, but we try to go as often as we can.
Play: Music is my 'non-web' related passion and before Finley arrived I was a regular on the local DJ circuit, I played at a number of bars and clubs in Colchester over a period of 12 years - I even spread my wings as far as London, Ibiza and Washington DC! Since Finley arrived I've gone back to being a bedroom DJ once again, I'm now happy to put together regular DJ mixes for my Musical Rant blog and I try to keep up to date with the scene as much as I can, but going out every weekend DJ'ing until the small hours is a little beyond me now! I also enjoy taking photographs from time to time, I don't take it too seriously and don't have the finances for fancy equipment, but I do really enjoy taking photos with my point and shoot Canon or my iPhone and putting the results up on my Flickr profile. And if that wasn't enough - I also design and sell T-Shirts on my Worm Sign T-Shirts store and design alternative movie posters for sale on my Society6 page.

By the age of 20 I've composed, recorded and produced over 8 hours of my original music, did many guest appearances, music for commercials, movies, TV series, produced and arranged for many great musicians.

Founder/Designer Fresh&Daily.Some older work here.View my Dribbbles.See my 100 Days of Hand-lettering ProjectRead my blog, and I sometimes write on Medium.I wrote an ebook on Freelancing hereI tweet often here, say hi!Listen to a podcast interview I did on Freelancing hereSharing photos (almost daily) on Instagram.More photos on FlickrYou can visit my Design Shop Creative MarketAnd if you like, you can view my CV/Resume.I have a love for type, sketching, paperbackbooks, gadgets, landscaping & DIY.I am an avid photographer and coffee drinker.My most important jobs, are that of Mommyto two amazing girls &Wife to a wonderful husband.

header: I tell stories in unexpected places.
bio:
They live on your phone, in your 'feed' or on the streets of your neighborhood.
I find emerging technologies and infuse them with narrative.
If the technology does not exist, I build it.
